Why an octopus?

Unlike many animals, an octopus naturally balances centralized intelligence with highly capable arms that can act semi-independently while remaining coordinated.

For Pantheon, that maps well to multiple specialized operators working toward one objective.

One mind.
Eight adaptive operators.

