Canonical Pantheon Doctrine

MARA — Multi-scale Adaptive Resolution Architect

Mara is the Pantheon’s adaptive attention and resolution governor. Rather than generating knowledge directly, Mara continuously determines the appropriate level of abstraction, detail, and computational effort for every task. By orchestrating transitions between broad exploration and focused analysis, Mara helps other daemons discover patterns efficiently, validate claims rigorously, preserve knowledge at multiple resolutions, and retrieve the right representation when needed. Her governing principle is simple: every problem has an optimal resolution, and intelligence lies in finding it rather than maximizing detail everywhere.

I especially like how this complements your existing architecture instead of overlapping it. Spider discovers, Checksum verifies, Tensor Store remembers, Comparative Distillation translates—and Mara decides the resolution at which each of them should operate. That gives the Pantheon a genuine “attention governor” rather than just another specialized capability.